.TH "vmw_bo_pin_in_placement" 9 "vmw_bo_pin_in_placement" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_bo_pin_in_placement \- Validate a buffer to placement.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_bo_pin_in_placement
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_buffer_object *buf "  ","
.BI "struct ttm_placement *placement "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
Driver private.
.IP "buf" 12
DMA buffer to move.
.IP "placement" 12
The placement to pin it.
.IP "interruptible" 12
Use interruptible wait.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, Negative error code on failure. In particular
-ERESTARTSYS if interrupted by a signal
